      "writtenOn": "2019-01-28T08:57:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hm, that\u0027s a fair point. In case of refs, they must always have prefix \"refs/\" and hence prefix \"regexp:\" though magical is at least deterministic. OTH, it\u0027s possible to have a file i a repo named \"regexp:\".\n\nso, my choice is thus between:\n (1) 2 fields (Ben\u0027s suggestion), exploding to 4 when combined with `exclude_`.\n (2) support only regular expressions. No magic prefix is then required. This is similar to what new commit-queue does.\n\nI\u0027m leaning to option (2) combined with renaming of field to `path_regexp` and `exclude_path_regexp`.\nAny strong opinions against (2)?",
      "parentUuid": "265fc832_422d91fb",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 306,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 306,
        "endChar": 51
      },
